But then DataBot or Positron Assistant sends a query that might incorporate that information

00:29:12.000 --> 00:29:17.760
to your model provider. And then the model provider sends that query to the LLM,

00:29:17.760 --> 00:29:22.319
but then might also do other things with it. It could use it for future model training,

00:29:22.319 --> 00:29:29.119
it might share it with third parties, and it might store your data. And all of these,

00:29:29.119 --> 00:29:33.439
those three things are in dotted lines, because those are maybes. Those aren't necessarily

00:29:34.319 --> 00:29:39.760
givens. And this is why it's very important for you or your organization to develop some

00:29:39.760 --> 00:29:45.280
kind of trust with whatever model provider you're using. So Posit doesn't store your data. I told

00:29:45.280 --> 00:29:50.880
you that the LLM itself doesn't store your data, but your provider might, depending on your

00:29:50.880 --> 00:29:58.239
or your organization's agreement. The good news is that zero data retention agreements,

00:29:58.239 --> 00:30:03.359
HIPAA compliant agreements, or other arrangements are relatively common for organizations to work

00:30:03.359 --> 00:30:08.640
out with model providers. So you can have an arrangement where they absolutely do not store

00:30:08.640 --> 00:30:16.959
your data, share it in any way, or use it for future training. But these are generally not

